    <summary>Oracle Instant Client sqlplus (instantclient-sqlplus)</summary>
    <description>This package installs Oracle Instant Client sqlplus according to your platform (x86 or x64).

        ## Package Specifics
        **The install will fail unless manual download of instant client zip file(s) is first completed!!!**
        NOTE: Package does not automate download of instant client file(s) from the source location of http://download.oracle.com/otn/ due to a mixture of cookies, redirects and password protection. Instant Client sqlplus must be manually downloaded to your web or file server and passed to the installer using the FROM_LOCATION package parameter on install OR downloaded to the default FROM_LOCATION of env:temp. Recommendation: Host instant client files on your internal network and provide a custom config for the installation of the instant client package to your users. For additional details see https://github.com/chocolatey/choco/wiki/CommandsInstall#packagesconfig.  Alternatively: Host package on your internal nuget server and change following variables for your environment: FROM_LOCATION, PROD_HOME, and machine.

        ### Package Parameters
        Package parameters should be passed using a hashtable syntax

        * `FROM_LOCATION` -  The location of the source of the products to be installed. Full directory path to instant client software. If not specified $env:temp is used. Note: file, http and ftp paths can be used. 
        Example: \\network\share\path\instantclient\120120
        * `PROD_HOME` - The local directory location for unzip. If not specified $env:ChocolateyInstall\lib\instantclient is used. PROD_HOME is the product location of the component on the target machine. The PROD_HOME variable is only used for non-Oracle Home components. Do NOT put Instant Client libraries in ORACLE_HOME directory. Put the Instant Client into a separate clean directory. 
        Example: PROD_HOME=C:\Oracle\product
        * `MACHINE` - Set this boolean variable to true to set the Instant Client directory path to a machine path env variable instead of default user env path variable.
        Example: MACHINE=true

Install according to platform
```
choco install instantclient-sqlplus-12_1 -packageParameters "-FROM_LOCATION  \\network\share\path\instantclient\120120 -PROD_HOME C:\Oracle\product"
```
If you want to install 32-bit InstantClient on 64-bit OS
```
choco install instantclient-sqlplus-12_1 -packageParameters "-FROM_LOCATION http://choco.local/instantclient -PROD_HOME C:\Oracle\product\x86" --forcex86
```
